The diameter can be calculated using the distance formula:
\begin{align*}
d &= \sqrt{{(x_1 - x_2)}^2+{(y_1-y_2)}^2} \\[3pt]
&= \sqrt{(6-0)^2 + (-4 - (-2))^2}\\[3pt]
&= \sqrt{(6)^2+(-2)^2} \\[3pt]
&= \sqrt{36 +4} \\[3pt]
&= \sqrt{40}\\[3pt]
&= 2\sqrt{10}
\end{align*}
The radius is half the diameter:
\[
r = \dfrac{d}{2} = 2\dfrac{\sqrt{10}}{2} = \sqrt{10}
\]

