For the $1$st expression, we have:
\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{DA}+\overrightarrow{AC}+\overrightarrow{CB}
&= (\overrightarrow{DA}+\overrightarrow{AC})+\overrightarrow{CB} \\[3pt]
&= \overrightarrow{DC}+\overrightarrow{CB} \\[3pt]
&= \overrightarrow{DB} \quad {\color{green}\checkmark}
\end{align*}
For the $2$nd expression, we have:
\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{DA}+\overrightarrow{AB}
&= \overrightarrow{DB} \quad {\color{green}\checkmark}
\end{align*}
For the $3$rd expression, we have:
\begin{align*}
\overrightarrow{BA}-\overrightarrow{CA}+\overrightarrow{CD}
&= (\overrightarrow{BA}-\overrightarrow{CA})+\overrightarrow{CD} \\[3pt]
&= (\overrightarrow{BA}+\overrightarrow{AC})+\overrightarrow{CD} \\[3pt]
&= \overrightarrow{BC}+\overrightarrow{CD} \\[3pt]
&= \overrightarrow{BD} \\[3pt]
&\neq \overrightarrow{DB} \quad {\color{red}\times}
\end{align*}
Therefore, the correct answer is "I and II only".

